nly validates TimeZone field changes (not on creation if unchanged from update)\n\n**TimeZone Validation** (validateTimeZone function):\n- Rejects nil or empty TimeZone strings\n- Validates IANA time zone naming convention using regex: `^[A-Za-z\\\\.\\-_0-9+]{1,14}$`\n- Prevents '.' and '..' directory components\n- Prevents components starting with '-'\n- Disallows legacy 'Local' time zone name (must be explicit IANA zone)\n- Verifies time zone can be loaded with time.LoadLocation()\n\n**Schedule Format Validation** (validateScheduleFormat function):\n- Validates cron expression format using cron.ParseStandard()\n- Enforces migration from TZ variable in schedule to timeZone field:\n  - Allows TZ in schedule only if oldSpec already had it (backward compatibility)\n  - Otherwise requires timeZone field instead of TZ/CRON_TZ in schedule\n\n## Storage and Strategy\n\n**CronJob Strategy** (pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/strategy.go):\n- cronJobStrategy implements creation/update validation and preparation\n- PrepareForCreate clears status, sets generation to 1\n- PrepareForUpdate preserves status, increments generation on spec changes\n- ValidateCronJob delegates to batchvalidation.ValidateCronJobCreate/Update\n- DefaultGarbageCollectionPolicy differs by version: OrphanDependents for v1beta1 (backward compat), DeleteDependents for v1\n- WarningsOnUpdate warns if TZ variable used in schedule instead of timeZone field (line 159-161)\n\nThe TimeZone field represents a key addition to the CronJob v1 specification, allowing explicit timezone support throughout the API, validation, and controller logic, while v1beta1 maintains backward compatibility with legacy patterns."
